{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":51,"text":"What I'm going to do is,\nI'm going to explain to you"},{"time":3014,"text":"an extreme green concept"},{"time":5066,"text":"that was developed\nat NASA's Glenn Research Center"},{"time":8058,"text":"in Cleveland, Ohio."},{"time":10060,"text":"But before I do that, we have to go over"},{"time":12490,"text":"the definition of what green is,"},{"time":14027,"text":"'cause a lot of us have a\ndifferent definition of it."},{"time":17024,"text":"Green. The product is created through"},{"time":19017,"text":"environmentally and socially\nconscious means."},{"time":21480,"text":"There's plenty of things that\nare being called green now."},{"time":24668,"text":"What does it actually mean?"},{"time":26280,"text":"We use three metrics to determine green."},{"time":29923,"text":"The first metric is: Is it sustainable?"},{"time":33015,"text":"Which means, are you preserving\nwhat you are doing for future use"},{"time":36539,"text":"or for future generations?"},{"time":39034,"text":"Is it alternative? Is it different\nthan what is being used today,"},{"time":43007,"text":"or does it have a lower carbon footprint"},{"time":45812,"text":"than what's used conventionally?"},{"time":48396,"text":"And three: Is it renewable?"},{"time":51231,"text":"Does it come from Earth's\nnatural replenishing resources,"},{"time":54987,"text":"such as sun, wind and water?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58087,"text":"Now, my task at NASA is to develop"},{"time":61619,"text":"the next generation of aviation fuels."},{"time":64815,"text":"Extreme green. Why aviation?"},{"time":67644,"text":"The field of aviation uses\nmore fuel than just about"},{"time":71001,"text":"every other combined. We\nneed to find an alternative."},{"time":76017,"text":"Also it's a national\naeronautics directive."},{"time":79017,"text":"One of the national aeronautics\ngoals is to develop"},{"time":81685,"text":"the next generation of fuels, biofuels,"},{"time":84381,"text":"using domestic and safe,\nfriendly resources."},{"time":88091,"text":"Now, combating that challenge"},{"time":90959,"text":"we have to also meet\nthe big three metric —"},{"time":93849,"text":"Actually, extreme green\nfor us is all three together;"},{"time":97662,"text":"that's why you see the plus\nthere. I was told to say that."},{"time":100052,"text":"So it has to be the big three at\nGRC. That's another metric."},{"time":105049,"text":"Ninety-seven percent of the\nworld's water is saltwater."},{"time":111000,"text":"How about we use that?\nCombine that with number three."},{"time":115010,"text":"Do not use arable land."},{"time":118042,"text":"Because crops are already\ngrowing on that land"},{"time":120222,"text":"that's very scarce around the world."},{"time":123019,"text":"Number two: Don't compete with food crops."},{"time":126026,"text":"That's already a well established\nentity, they don't need another entry."},{"time":130443,"text":"And lastly the most precious\nresource we have on this Earth"},{"time":134391,"text":"is fresh water. Don't use fresh water."},{"time":139051,"text":"If 97.5 percent\nof the world's water is saltwater,"},{"time":142022,"text":"2.5 percent is fresh water.\nLess than a half percent"},{"time":145299,"text":"of that is accessible for human use."},{"time":147060,"text":"But 60 percent of the population\nlives within that one percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151021,"text":"So, combating my problem was,\nnow I have to be extreme green"},{"time":156013,"text":"and meet the big three.\nLadies and gentlemen,"},{"time":158261,"text":"welcome to the GreenLab Research Facility."},{"time":162007,"text":"This is a facility dedicated\nto the next generation"},{"time":164942,"text":"of aviation fuels using halophytes."},{"time":168087,"text":"A halophyte is a salt-tolerating plant."},{"time":171065,"text":"Most plants don't like salt,\nbut halophytes tolerate salt."},{"time":175093,"text":"We also are using weeds"},{"time":178088,"text":"and we are also using algae."},{"time":181019,"text":"The good thing about our lab is, we've had"},{"time":183010,"text":"3,600 visitors in the last two years."},{"time":186020,"text":"Why do you think that's so?"},{"time":188022,"text":"Because we are on to something special."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192028,"text":"So, in the lower you see\nthe GreenLab obviously,"},{"time":194597,"text":"and on the right hand\nside you'll see algae."},{"time":197049,"text":"If you are into the business\nof the next generation"},{"time":200002,"text":"of aviation fuels, algae\nis a viable option,"},{"time":202322,"text":"there's a lot of funding right now,"},{"time":204001,"text":"and we have an algae to fuels program."},{"time":206022,"text":"There's two types of algae growing."},{"time":208022,"text":"One is a closed photobioreactor\nthat you see here,"},{"time":211015,"text":"and what you see on the other\nside is our species —"},{"time":215036,"text":"we are currently using a species\ncalled Scenedesmus dimorphus."},{"time":219006,"text":"Our job at NASA is to take the\nexperimental and computational"},{"time":223312,"text":"and make a better mixing for\nthe closed photobioreactors."},{"time":228007,"text":"Now the problems with closed\nphotobioreactors are:"},{"time":230044,"text":"They are quite expensive,\nthey are automated,"},{"time":232775,"text":"and it's very difficult\nto get them in large scale."},{"time":235803,"text":"So on large scale what do they use?"},{"time":237428,"text":"We use open pond systems.\nNow, around the world"},{"time":240921,"text":"they are growing algae,\nwith this racetrack design"},{"time":244442,"text":"that you see here. Looks like an oval with"},{"time":246891,"text":"a paddle wheel and mixes really well,"},{"time":249028,"text":"but when it gets around the last turn,\nwhich I call turn four — it's stagnant."},{"time":253086,"text":"We actually have a solution for that."},{"time":255076,"text":"In the GreenLab in our open pond system"},{"time":258040,"text":"we use something that happens\nin nature: waves."},{"time":261055,"text":"We actually use wave technology\non our open pond systems."},{"time":264747,"text":"We have 95 percent mixing\nand our lipid content is higher"},{"time":269431,"text":"than a closed photobioreactor system,"},{"time":272049,"text":"which we think is significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274030,"text":"There is a drawback to algae,\nhowever: It's very expensive."},{"time":278062,"text":"Is there a way to produce\nalgae inexpensively?"},{"time":283165,"text":"And the answer is: yes."},{"time":285026,"text":"We do the same thing\nwe do with halophytes,"},{"time":288049,"text":"and that is: climatic adaptation."},{"time":292004,"text":"In our GreenLab we have\nsix primary ecosystems"},{"time":294816,"text":"that range from freshwater\nall the way to saltwater."},{"time":298787,"text":"What we do: We take a potential\nspecies, we start at freshwater,"},{"time":302546,"text":"we add a little bit more salt,\nwhen the second tank here"},{"time":305274,"text":"will be the same ecosystem as Brazil —"},{"time":307406,"text":"right next to the sugar cane\nfields you can have our plants —"},{"time":310502,"text":"the next tank represents Africa,\nthe next tank represents Arizona,"},{"time":314745,"text":"the next tank represents Florida,"},{"time":317056,"text":"and the next tank represents\nCalifornia or the open ocean."},{"time":320919,"text":"What we are trying to do is to\ncome up with a single species"},{"time":325014,"text":"that can survive anywhere in the\nworld, where there's barren desert."},{"time":331019,"text":"We are being very successful so far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333057,"text":"Now, here's one of the problems."},{"time":335701,"text":"If you are a farmer, you need five things\nto be successful: You need seeds,"},{"time":341428,"text":"you need soil, you need\nwater and you need sun,"},{"time":345043,"text":"and the last thing that you\nneed is fertilizer."},{"time":348613,"text":"Most people use chemical fertilizers.\nBut guess what?"},{"time":352168,"text":"We do not use chemical fertilizer."},{"time":354868,"text":"Wait a second! I just saw lots of greenery\nin your GreenLab. You have to use fertilizer."},{"time":360023,"text":"Believe it or not, in our analysis\nof our saltwater ecosystems"},{"time":364228,"text":"80 percent of what we need\nare in these tanks themselves."},{"time":368028,"text":"The 20 percent that's missing\nis nitrogen and phosphorous."},{"time":372027,"text":"We have a natural solution: fish."},{"time":374083,"text":"No we don't cut up the fish\nand put them in there."},{"time":377971,"text":"Fish waste is what we use.\nAs a matter of fact"},{"time":381854,"text":"we use freshwater mollies, that we've\nused our climatic adaptation technique"},{"time":386019,"text":"from freshwater all the way to seawater."},{"time":389041,"text":"Freshwater mollies: cheap,\nthey love to make babies,"},{"time":396037,"text":"and they love to go to the bathroom."},{"time":397846,"text":"And the more they go to the\nbathroom, the more fertilizer we get,"},{"time":400001,"text":"the better off we are, believe it or not."},{"time":402540,"text":"It should be noted that we use\nsand as our soil,"},{"time":407805,"text":"regular beach sand. Fossilized coral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412030,"text":"So a lot of people ask me,\n\"How did you get started?\""},{"time":416001,"text":"Well, we got started in what we\ncall the indoor biofuels lab."},{"time":421006,"text":"It's a seedling lab. We have 26\ndifferent species of halophytes,"},{"time":425412,"text":"and five are winners. What we do here is —"},{"time":428684,"text":"actually it should be called\na death lab, 'cause we try to"},{"time":431509,"text":"kill the seedlings, make them rough —"},{"time":434098,"text":"and then we come to the GreenLab."},{"time":436418,"text":"What you see in the lower corner"},{"time":438176,"text":"is a wastewater treatment plant experiment"},{"time":440364,"text":"that we are growing, a macro-algae\nthat I'll talk about in a minute."},{"time":444057,"text":"And lastly, it's me actually working\nin the lab to prove to you I do work,"},{"time":448043,"text":"I don't just talk about what I do."},{"time":451775,"text":"Here's the plant species.\nSalicornia virginica."},{"time":455005,"text":"It's a wonderful plant. I love that plant."},{"time":458564,"text":"Everywhere we go we see it. It's\nall over the place, from Maine"},{"time":462030,"text":"all the way to California.\nWe love that plant."},{"time":465041,"text":"Second is Salicornia bigelovii. Very\ndifficult to get around the world."},{"time":470006,"text":"It is the highest lipid\ncontent that we have,"},{"time":472052,"text":"but it has a shortcoming: It's short."},{"time":476042,"text":"Now you take europaea, which is the\nlargest or the tallest plant that we have."},{"time":481163,"text":"And what we are trying to do"},{"time":483081,"text":"with natural selection or adaptive\nbiology — combine all three"},{"time":487462,"text":"to make a high-growth, high-lipid plant."},{"time":491578,"text":"Next, when a hurricane decimated the\nDelaware Bay — soybean fields gone —"},{"time":498842,"text":"we came up with an idea:\nCan you have a plant"},{"time":501706,"text":"that has a land reclamation positive\nin Delaware? And the answer is yes."},{"time":507017,"text":"It's called seashore mallow.\nKosteletzkya virginica —"},{"time":510991,"text":"say that five times fast if you can."},{"time":514009,"text":"This is a 100 percent usable plant. The\nseeds: biofuels. The rest: cattle feed."},{"time":521597,"text":"It's there for 10 years;\nit's working very well."},{"time":525036,"text":"Now we get to Chaetomorpha."},{"time":528363,"text":"This is a macro-algae that loves"},{"time":531585,"text":"excess nutrients. If you\nare in the aquarium industry"},{"time":534007,"text":"you know we use it\nto clean up dirty tanks."},{"time":536818,"text":"This species is so significant to us."},{"time":541029,"text":"The properties are very close to plastic."},{"time":545000,"text":"We are trying right now to convert\nthis macro-algae into a bioplastic."},{"time":550378,"text":"If we are successful, we will\nrevolutionize the plastics industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555051,"text":"So, we have a seed to fuel program."},{"time":558573,"text":"We have to do something with\nthis biomass that we have."},{"time":561530,"text":"And so we do G.C. extraction, lipid\noptimization, so on and so forth,"},{"time":566039,"text":"because our goal really is to come up with"},{"time":569726,"text":"the next generation of aviation fuels,\naviation specifics, so on and so forth."},{"time":573636,"text":"So far we talked about water and fuel,"},{"time":578056,"text":"but along the way we found out\nsomething interesting about Salicornia:"},{"time":585000,"text":"It's a food product."},{"time":588686,"text":"So we talk about ideas\nworth spreading, right?"},{"time":591499,"text":"How about this: In sub-Saharan\nAfrica, next to the sea, saltwater,"},{"time":598353,"text":"barren desert,\nhow about we take that plant,"},{"time":603212,"text":"plant it, half use for food,\nhalf use for fuel."},{"time":608044,"text":"We can make that happen, inexpensively."},{"time":611845,"text":"You can see\nthere's a greenhouse in Germany"},{"time":614543,"text":"that sells it as a health food product."},{"time":617007,"text":"This is harvested, and in the middle here\nis a shrimp dish, and it's being pickled."},{"time":622233,"text":"So I have to tell you a joke.\nSalicornia is known as sea beans,"},{"time":626846,"text":"saltwater asparagus and pickle weed."},{"time":630319,"text":"So we are pickling pickle\nweed in the middle."},{"time":633050,"text":"Oh, I thought it was funny. (Laughter)"},{"time":635852,"text":"And at the bottom is seaman's mustard.\nIt does make sense,"},{"time":639225,"text":"this is a logical snack. You have mustard,"},{"time":641612,"text":"you are a seaman, you see the\nhalophyte, you mix it together,"},{"time":644760,"text":"it's a great snack with some crackers."},{"time":647022,"text":"And last, garlic with Salicornia,\nwhich is what I like."},{"time":654022,"text":"So, water, fuel and food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658997,"text":"None of this is possible\nwithout the GreenLab team."},{"time":662548,"text":"Just like the Miami Heat has the big\nthree, we have the big three at NASA GRC."},{"time":667529,"text":"That's myself, professor Bob Hendricks,\nour fearless leader, and Dr. Arnon Chait."},{"time":673008,"text":"The backbone of the GreenLab is students."},{"time":677537,"text":"Over the last two years\nwe've had 35 different students"},{"time":681452,"text":"from around the world working at GreenLab."},{"time":684607,"text":"As a matter fact my division chief says\na lot, \"You have a green university.\""},{"time":689016,"text":"I say, \"I'm okay with that,\n'cause we are nurturing"},{"time":691551,"text":"the next generation of extreme\ngreen thinkers, which is significant.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":696575,"text":"So, in first summary I presented\nto you what we think"},{"time":701896,"text":"is a global solution\nfor food, fuel and water."},{"time":708023,"text":"There's something missing to be complete."},{"time":711017,"text":"Clearly we use electricity.\nWe have a solution for you —"},{"time":715808,"text":"We're using clean energy sources here."},{"time":719057,"text":"So, we have two wind turbines\nconnected to the GreenLab,"},{"time":723478,"text":"we have four or five more\nhopefully coming soon."},{"time":727005,"text":"We are also using something\nthat is quite interesting —"},{"time":730615,"text":"there is a solar array field at\nNASA's Glenn Research Center,"},{"time":735238,"text":"hasn't been used for 15 years."},{"time":738380,"text":"Along with some of my electrical\nengineering colleagues,"},{"time":741143,"text":"we realized that they are still viable,"},{"time":743286,"text":"so we are refurbishing them right now."},{"time":746042,"text":"In about 30 days or so they'll be\nconnected to the GreenLab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751078,"text":"And the reason why you see\nred, red and yellow, is"},{"time":754004,"text":"a lot of people think NASA employees\ndon't work on Saturday —"},{"time":757271,"text":"This is a picture taken on Saturday."},{"time":760189,"text":"There are no cars around, but you see my truck\nin yellow. I work on Saturday. (Laughter)"},{"time":764814,"text":"This is a proof to you that I'm working."},{"time":766647,"text":"'Cause we do what it takes to get the\njob done, most people know that."},{"time":770547,"text":"Here's a concept with this:"},{"time":773425,"text":"We are using the GreenLab\nfor a micro-grid test bed"},{"time":778981,"text":"for the smart grid concept in Ohio."},{"time":783044,"text":"We have the ability to do that,\nand I think it's going to work."},{"time":788951,"text":"So, GreenLab Research Facility."},{"time":794044,"text":"A self-sustainable renewable energy\necosystem was presented today."},{"time":799067,"text":"We really, really hope this\nconcept catches on worldwide."},{"time":805014,"text":"We think we have a solution for food,\nwater, fuel and now energy. Complete."},{"time":814064,"text":"It's extreme green, it's sustainable,\nalternative and renewable"},{"time":820189,"text":"and it meets the big three at GRC:"},{"time":824027,"text":"Don't use arable land, don't\ncompete with food crops,"},{"time":829018,"text":"and most of all, don't use fresh water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832080,"text":"So I get a lot of questions about,\n\"What are you doing in that lab?\""},{"time":837054,"text":"And I usually say, \"None of your business,\nthat's what I'm doing in the lab.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":842807,"text":"And believe it or not, my number one goal"},{"time":846350,"text":"for working on this project is"},{"time":849060,"text":"I want to help save the world."}]}]}